### File Descriptions
```
app.py
- The main backend Python application file.
- Implements the web server, routing, and all business logic.
- Handles reading from and writing to the local text files in the 'data' directory.
- Manages user sessions, course enrollment, progress tracking, assignment submissions, and certificate generation.
- Uses a Python web framework (e.g., Flask) to serve HTML templates and handle form submissions.

data/
- Directory containing all persistent data files in text format as specified.
- Each file corresponds to a data entity (users, courses, enrollments, assignments, submissions, certificates).

templates/
- Contains all HTML template files for the nine pages defined in the requirements.
- Each template corresponds to a page and includes the specified elements with their IDs.
- Templates use templating syntax to dynamically render data passed from app.py.

static/
- Contains static assets such as CSS and JavaScript files.
- css/styles.css: Stylesheet for consistent styling across all pages.
- js/scripts.js: JavaScript for client-side interactivity (e.g., button actions, form validation).

This structure keeps the backend logic consolidated in a single Python file for simplicity and maintainability, while separating frontend templates and static assets for clarity and modularity.
```"

